### Solution Walkthrough:



#### Before:
```dart
// mobile/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart
class _DashboardScreenState extends ... with SingleTickerProviderStateMixin {
  int _pendingChangesCount = 0;
  late AnimationController _syncAnimationController;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    _syncAnimationController = AnimationController(...);
    _loadPendingChangesCount(); // Manual fetch
  }

  Future<void> _loadPendingChangesCount() async {
    final count = await ref.read(databaseProvider).select(...).get();
    if (mounted) setState(() { _pendingChangesCount = count.length; });
  }

  Future<void> _triggerImmediateSync(...) async {
    // ...
    await _loadPendingChangesCount(); // Manual refresh
    // ...
    if (mounted) await _loadPendingChangesCount(); // Manual refresh again
  }
}

```



#### After:
```dart
// new file: sync_ui_state_provider.dart
class SyncUiState {
  final int pendingChangesCount;
  // ... other UI-related state
}

final syncUiStateProvider = StreamProvider<SyncUiState>((ref) {
  final db = ref.watch(databaseProvider);
  // Listen to outbox changes and other sync streams
  return db.select(db.outbox).watch().map((items) {
    return SyncUiState(pendingChangesCount: items.length);
  });
});

// mobile/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart
class _DashboardScreenState extends ... {
  // No more _pendingChangesCount or _loadPendingChangesCount()

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final syncUiState = ref.watch(syncUiStateProvider);
    final pendingChangesCount = syncUiState.value?.pendingChangesCount ?? 0;
    // ... use pendingChangesCount to build the UI
  }
}

```




<details><summary>Suggestion importance[1-10]: 8</summary>

__

Why: This is a strong architectural suggestion that correctly identifies the mixing of UI and data-fetching logic within the `DashboardScreen`. Centralizing UI state would simplify the widget, improve maintainability, and create a more robust, reactive state management pattern.


